The paper proposes a new concept of secure list decoding, which involves additional security conditions beyond conventional list decoding. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the information theory (cs.IT), cryptography (cs.CR), and coding theory (cs.CC) sub-categories. The paper also mentions the use of this protocol for anonymous auction, which suggests that it may also belong to the distributed systems (cs.DS) and social and information networks (cs.SI) sub-categories.
